SUMMARY:Sunday Worship Service
DESCRIPTION:Worship This Sunday \nThe Book of Job: Broken Hallelujahs\n“Why?”\nSunday\, March 22\, 2026\n10:30 a.m. in the Sanctuary & Online \nThis Sunday\, we continue our Lenten sermon series\, The Book of Job: Broken Hallelujahs\, a journey through the raw\, honest faith of Job. Senior Pastor Derek Zeyl will preach from Job 42\, where Job encounters God’s overwhelming presence and responds with humility\, trust\, and a renewed understanding of God’s goodness\, even without receiving the tidy “why” he longed for. \nWhat to Expect\n\nSpirit-led worship with Scripture\, song\, and prayer\nA thoughtful\, engaging sermon rooted in the teachings of Jesus\nChildren’s and Youth programs available during the service\nFellowship Hour upstairs following worship\n\nScripture for This Sunday\nJob 42 \n\nA chapter where Job moves from questioning to surrender\, discovering that God’s wisdom holds more than easy explanations ever could and that restoration begins with relationship.\n\nJoin Us on Sunday\nWe’d love to worship with you\, whether in person or online. If you’re visiting for the first time\, welcome! We hope you’ll feel at home as we gather to seek God together\, bring our honest questions\, and discover the hope woven through Job’s story and our own.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/march-22-sunday-worship-service/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event,Worship Service
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/worshipService800x600.jpg
END:VEVENT
