SUMMARY:Lenten Small Group March 23
DESCRIPTION:This is the final of five meetings taking place at FPCE on Mondays during Lent. This ‘pop-up’ small group is forming for those interested in using the lectio divina and visio divina methods to contemplate the Bible passage that is the topic of each week’s sermon and a related piece of art. This group will meet during Lent on Mondays at 9:30 a.m.\, both in person in Room 213 and on Zoom. All are welcome to join this peaceful opportunity to meditate on Scripture. Contact Valrie Barrett valrie924@gmail.com or Beth Rice rice.beth.l@gmail.com for details on how to take part. \nWant to join on Zoom? Join here: https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85398693001?pwd=TfbcLXibwYbfJfKvFYmPmBWdZulVaj.1 \nWhat’s a ‘pop-up’ group? \nA pop-up group is one that is only around for a short time or a specific season (it pops up and then it’s gone). These are open to anyone\, and are especially terrific for those who are new to First Pres Evanston\, or are not currently involved in one of our small groups.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/lenten-small-group-march-23/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event,Small Group
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/LentBibleGroup_800x600EventTile.jpg
END:VEVENT
