SUMMARY:Palm Sunday Donkey Procession & Parade
DESCRIPTION:Start Palm Sunday with joy and community! First Presbyterian Church of Evanston will join with other local congregations for an ecumenical Palm Sunday procession around Raymond Square (right across from our church at Chicago & Lake). Together we’ll celebrate with music\, wave palms\, and walk with a live donkey\, remembering Jesus’ entry into Jerusalem.\n\nAll are welcome\, neighbors\, families\, and friends! \n\n\nEvent Details\n\nDate: Sunday\, March 29\nTime: 9 a.m.\nLocation: Raymond Square\, Evanston (across from First Pres\, Chicago Ave & Lake St)\n\n\nWhat to Expect\n\n\nHymns and music led by participating congregations\nWaving of palms (palms provided)\nA short\, family-friendly walk around the square\nA live donkey leading the procession\nA warm\, community-centered start to Holy Week\n\n\nAfter the Parade\nAs we begin Holy Week\, we warmly invite you to worship with us at First Presbyterian Church of Evanston. You’re welcome to join us just across the street.  Click here for details about our Palm Sunday Worship Service. \nAnd learn more about all that’s happening this season:\nVisit our Easter Sunday page for full Holy Week and Easter information.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/palm-sunday-donkey-procession-parade/
LOCATION:IL
CATEGORIES:Featured Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/donkeyProcession-800-x-600.jpg
END:VEVENT
