SUMMARY:Palm Sunday Worship Service
DESCRIPTION:Hosanna! Blessed is the One who comes in the name of the Lord. \n\nSunday\, March 29\nWorship at 10:30 a.m. — First Presbyterian Church of Evanston \n\nExplore all our Easter events\n\n\nBegin Holy Week with Us\nPalm Sunday marks the beginning of Holy Week—a time when we journey with Jesus toward the cross and the promise of new life. In worship we remember the crowds who welcomed Jesus into Jerusalem with palm branches and cries of “Hosanna!” while also hearing the deeper call of discipleship as Jesus speaks about His coming glorification. \nWhether you’ve been part of First Pres for years or you’re exploring faith for the first time\, you are warmly invited to worship with us. \n\n\n\nScripture for the Day\nJohn 12:12–27 \nIn this powerful passage we encounter: \n\nJesus entering Jerusalem as the crowds wave palms and celebrate Him as King\nThe unexpected request of Greek seekers who want to see Jesus\nJesus declaring that “the hour has come” for the Son of Man to be glorified\nThe image of a grain of wheat that must fall into the earth and die to bear much fruit\nA call to follow Him in a life shaped by self‑giving love\n\nThis text invites us to hold celebration and sacrifice together—to recognize Jesus as King while also embracing the path He walks toward the cross. \n\n\n\nWhat to Expect in Worship\n\nPalm branches for all ages\nScripture reading: John 12:12–27\nSermon reflecting on Jesus’ entry into Jerusalem and His call to disciples\nMusic led by our worship team and choir\nPrayers for Holy Week\nOpportunities for families to engage with the story\n\nChildren and families are especially welcome. \n\n\n\n\nHoly Week Invitation\nPalm Sunday invites us into the full journey of Holy Week.\nWe hope you will join us for: \n\nMaundy Thursday\nGood Friday\nEaster Sunday Celebration\n\n\n\n\nPlan Your Visit\n\nLocation: First Presbyterian Church of Evanston — 1427 Chicago Ave\, Evanston\nParking: Parking lot next to the church and street parking\nAccessibility: Accessible entrances and seating available\nLivestream Information: https://live.firstpresevanston.org/
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/palm-sunday-worship-service/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Palm-Sunday800x600.jpg
END:VEVENT
