SUMMARY:Maundy Thursday Meal and Communion Worship Service
DESCRIPTION:“Having loved his own who were in the world\, he loved them to the end.” — John 13:1 \n\nThursday\, April 2\n6 p.m. Dinner • 7 p.m. Worship\nDining Room\, 2nd Floor — First Presbyterian Church of Evanston\n\n\nExplore all our Easter Events\n\n\nJoin Us for a Meaningful Evening\nJoin us for a special Maundy Thursday Service as we gather in the spirit of the Last Supper. This reflective evening brings us into the Upper Room\, remembering Jesus’ love\, humility\, and service as described in John 13:1–17. \n\nTogether we’ll share a simple meal\, celebrate Communion\, and enter the heart of Holy Week with prayer and quiet reflection. \nEveryone is warmly invited to this meaningful time of fellowship and worship. \n\n\n\nScripture for the Night\nJohn 13:1–17\nThis passage shows us: \n\nJesus’ unwavering love for His disciples\nHis humility and willingness to serve\nPeter’s struggle to understand what Jesus is doing\nJesus’ invitation to follow His pattern of love\nA call to see service not as a gesture\, but as a way of life\n\nThis text reminds us that the heart of Holy Week is found in love embodied. \n\n\nA Shared Meal\nA central part of our Maundy Thursday observance is gathering around a meal\, remembering the fellowship Jesus shared with His disciples. \nDuring the meal\, we will: \n\nSit together at tables\nShare conversation and quiet moments\nHear Scripture and reflections\nMove gently into the Communion liturgy\n\nThis simple act echoes the warmth\, intimacy\, and community of the Upper Room. \n\n\nParking & Accessibility\n\nParking Lot: Located next to the church\nStreet Parking: Available around the neighborhood\nAccessible Entrances\nLivestream: https://live.firstpresevanston.org/
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/maundy-thursday-meal-and-communion-worship-service/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/MaundyThursday-2024.jpg
END:VEVENT
