SUMMARY:Good Friday Service
DESCRIPTION:“It is finished.” — John 19:30 \nFriday\, April 3\n7 p.m. — Sanctuary\nFirst Presbyterian Church of Evanston\n1427 Chicago Ave\, Evanston \n\nExplore all of our Easter events \n\n\nA Night to Remember Christ’s Sacrifice\nJoin us for our Good Friday Service as we reflect on the depth and meaning of Jesus’ crucifixion. This solemn and contemplative gathering invites us to sit with the weight of the story found in John 18–19\, listening to the narrative of Jesus’ arrest\, trial\, suffering\, and death on the cross. \nThis is a quiet\, reverent service rooted in Scripture\, prayer\, and stillness as we prepare our hearts for the hope of Easter. \nAll are welcome to this sacred evening of worship. \n\nScripture for the Night\nJohn 18–19\nThroughout these chapters we encounter: \n\nJesus’ arrest in the garden\nPeter’s denial\nJesus before the high priest and before Pilate\nThe crowds calling for His crucifixion\nJesus’ suffering and death\nHis final words: “It is finished.”\n\nThis powerful narrative invites us to remember the cost of love and the breadth of God’s mercy. \n\nWhat to Expect\nThe service will include: \n\nA dramatic Scripture reading of John 18–19\nReflective music\nMoments of silence and stillness\nA brief meditation\nA quiet\, reverent atmosphere suitable for contemplation\n\nThe tone remains solemn and prayerful throughout the evening. \n\nParking & Accessibility\n\nParking lot next to the church\nStreet parking nearby\nAccessible entrances\nLivestream https://live.firstpresevanston.org/
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/good-friday-service/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/good-friday-800-x-600.jpg
END:VEVENT
